  "slug": "pretzel-rolls",
  "title": "Pretzel rolls",
  "subtitle": "Bavarian-style rolls with a chewy alkaline crust",
  "excerpt": "Pretzel rolls get their distinctive dark crust and chewy texture from a bicarbonate of soda bath before baking, a safer home-kitchen alternative to the food-grade lye used in professional bakeries. The characteristic slash across the top is cut just before the oven.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Pretzel-shaped baked goods have been documented in German-speaking Europe since the medieval period. The pretzel roll (Laugenbrötchen) is the twentieth-century bakery form, documented in German domestic cookery and widely adapted for home use with bicarbonate of soda as a substitute for the traditional lye bath.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The dark, shiny crust of a pretzel roll comes from the alkaline poaching step. Traditional pretzels use food-grade lye, but a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "baked soda bath",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpb8chy20000xcv4vi8sesy2"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " (a high concentration of bicarbonate of soda dissolved in boiling water) produces a similar effect. The dough itself is a firm, low-hydration white dough; the chewy texture comes from the crust, not from the crumb.",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "tip"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Use oiled baking paper rather than plain, the rolls stick if the paper isn't greased. The bicarbonate solution discolours aluminium pans, so use a stainless steel or non-reactive pot for the bath.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Dough"
            },
            "content": [
